lead_paragraph: HERMOSILLO, Mexico — The heavy-set man swept through a curtain into the reserved area of a nightclub as his bodyguard stood nearby. In the darkness, he agreed to talk about his business: handling the income from smuggling migrants across a 375-mile stretch of the U.S.-Mexico border.
headline_main: What Crackdown? Migrant Smuggling Business Adapts, Thrives

abstract: The tensions rising between Iran and the United States aren’t a signal that diplomacy will fail. They are a warning that negotiations are a must — and soon.
snippet: The tensions rising between Iran and the United States aren’t a signal that diplomacy will fail. They are a warning that negotiations are a must — and soon.
lead_paragraph: The momentous protests in Iran this autumn came at a delicate time in a tense standoff between the United States and Iran. Despite the recent prisoner swap, officials in Washington may see the prospects for diplomacy dimming. But that would be wrong. Iranian elections are coming, and without any American agreement to relent on sanctions, the current relatively conciliatory government might well lose all its influence in favor of far more confrontational hard-liners.

abstract: The Ukraine charge gets all the attention, but the article of impeachment about obstruction is just as urgent.
snippet: The Ukraine charge gets all the attention, but the article of impeachment about obstruction is just as urgent.
lead_paragraph: President Trump has just become the third president to be impeached by the House of Representatives. In a largely party-line vote, the House majority has sought to hold the president to account for how he has used the powers of his office.

abstract: A Denver radio station has canceled a scheduled program after one of the hosts said a school shooting would help break up media coverage of impeachment proceedings.
snippet: A Denver radio station has canceled a scheduled program after one of the hosts said a school shooting would help break up media coverage of impeachment proceedings.
lead_paragraph: DENVER — A Denver radio station has canceled a scheduled program after one of the hosts said a school shooting would help break up media coverage of impeachment proceedings.
headline_main: Radio Show Canceled After Host Makes School Shooting Comment
headline_print_headline: Radio Show Canceled After Host Makes School Shooting Comment
